OperandStack

Class OperandStack

  • java.lang.Object
    • OperandStack.OperandStack

  • public class OperandStack
extends java.lang.Object
    A stack for doing arithmetic and logic operations. Stack elements are of type Value.

    • Method Detail

      • push

        public void push(Value e)
        Pushes one element of type Value on to the operand stack and increments the stack pointer (sp) by one.

        stack before push: .... X
        push(Y);
        stack after push: .... X Y

        An error is signaled if no more room is available on the stack.

        Parameters:
        e - An object of the Value type to be placed on the stack.

      • pop

        public Value pop()
        Pops one element of type Value off the operand stack and decrements the stack pointer (sp) by one.

        stack before pop: .... X Y
        Z = pop();
        stack after pop: .... X
        and Z = Y

        An error is signaled if the stack is empty.

        Returns:
        Returns an object of type Value.

      • peek

        public Value peek(int n)
        Returns the n'th element on the stack (counted from the top) without removing it.
        Parameters:
        n - The index (counting from the top of the stack) of the element to be returned. The top element is at index 1.
